spans.text: ! slow Suspicion by his side , With winking , microscopic eye
The patient sufferer of a smile
the wound , Or Piety's soft incense
the wound , Or Piety's soft incense
those fell pangs which he endures , Nor Time forgets , nor Kindness
to shun The splendid glories of the sun
not a ray the gloom pervades
Where not a ray the gloom pervades
no peace he knows , His feverish blood , no calmer flows ;
Where Contemplation may retreat , And Silence take his mossy seat
for the dagger in his breast , And gripes it beneath his ruffled vest

Ah , hapless wretch ! condemned to know , The sad varieties of woe ; Wherever thy footsteps turn , to meet , An earthquake yawning at thy feet , While over thy head pale meteors glare , And boding tempests
